\">scratched\u003C/rs>\n                                    \u003Cp/>\n                                    \u003Cdamage ana=\"#text_condition.incomplete\"/>\n                                \u003C/layout>\n                            \u003C/layoutDesc>\n                        \u003C/objectDesc>\n                        \u003ChandDesc>\n                            \u003ChandNote>\n                                \u003C!-- Based on Glyph table: the ductus of the letters is comparable with other mid-6th century inscriptions but seems aberrant in the Geloan context. \n                                    The first nu has a different ductus from the second, which could perhaps lead to the hypothesis (although this difference in ductus between the same \n                                    letter in graffiti is not unusual) that it is not a nu? The letter in Selinus has the value of beta (cf. beta23) and with this value probably occurs in Segesta \n                                    in the Elymian inscriptions of Grotta Vanella (cf. e.g. ISic020114, 115, 118, 190).-->\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line1\">Line 1\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\"/>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                            \u003C/handNote>\n                        \u003C/handDesc>\n                    \u003C/physDesc>\n                    \u003Chistory>\n                        \u003Corigin>\n                            \u003CorigPlace>\u003Cregion>Sicilia\u003C/region>\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"ancient\" ref=\"https://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462214\">Gela\u003C/placeName>\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"modern\" ref=\"http://sws.geonames.org/2524653/\">Gela\u003C/placeName>\n                                \u003Cgeo>37.0630925, 14.2584705\u003C/geo>\n               